ty1250SysType.name: ty1250SysType
ty1250SysType.description: A textual description of the system model identifier. for example: TYLINK1250

ty1250SysSoftRev.name: ty1250SysSoftRev
ty1250SysSoftRev.description: Displays the Software Revision installed in this node.

ty1250SysHardRev.name: ty1250SysHardRev
ty1250SysHardRev.description: Displays the Hardware Revision of the node.

ty1250SysNumNetInstalled.name: ty1250SysNumNetInstalled
ty1250SysNumNetInstalled.description: The number of Network (DDS) ports that are installed. There is 1 on the 1250.

ty1250SysNumDteInstalled.name: ty1250SysNumDteInstalled
ty1250SysNumDteInstalled.description: The number of channels (DTE) that are installed. There is 1 on the 1250.

ty1250SysNumMaintInstalled.name: ty1250SysNumMaintInstalled
ty1250SysNumMaintInstalled.description: The number of Maintenance ports that are installed. There are 2 on the 1250.

ty1250SysName.name: ty1250SysName
ty1250SysName.description: The user supplied name of the node. This object does not affect operation, but may be useful for network management.

ty1250CfgAppClockSource.name: ty1250CfgAppClockSource
ty1250CfgAppClockSource.description: Default timing, or clock, source. There must be only one source on a DDS line. Node should always be network (2) timed on a point-to-network application. Line Driver applications need one node as internal (1), one as network (2).

ty1250CfgAppCircuitId.name: ty1250CfgAppCircuitId
ty1250CfgAppCircuitId.description: Circuit identifier provided by the service provider.

ty1250CfgNetType.name: ty1250CfgNetType
ty1250CfgNetType.description: Indicates type of service purchased on the attached network line (DDS or SW56). Valid selections are dedicated (1) and switch56 (2).

ty1250CfgNetGlareType.name: ty1250CfgNetGlareType
ty1250CfgNetGlareType.description: In switched applications, defines who wins when there are simultanious incomming and outgoing calls. If in doubt, select external-glare (2).

ty1250CfgNetEchoCan.name: ty1250CfgNetEchoCan
ty1250CfgNetEchoCan.description: In switched applications, some carriers, such as Sprint, require you to disable-echo-cancellors (2) for data apps on most lines. Calls take longer to come up when disabling is done; use ignore-echo-cancellers (1) on clear channel lines.

ty1250CfgNetAnsMode.name: ty1250CfgNetAnsMode
ty1250CfgNetAnsMode.description: In switched applications, allows for manual-answer (1) or automatic-answer (2) of inbound calls. Calls may be answered in manual mode via vt100, DTR, or the front panel button if so configured.

ty1250CfgNetDialTimeout.name: ty1250CfgNetDialTimeout
ty1250CfgNetDialTimeout.description: In switched applications, time in seconds to wait for far end to answer before giving up, and possibly redialing.

ty1250CfgNetNumRedial.name: ty1250CfgNetNumRedial
ty1250CfgNetNumRedial.description: In switched applications, number of times to redial if the call fails.

ty1250CfgNetRedialDelay.name: ty1250CfgNetRedialDelay
ty1250CfgNetRedialDelay.description: In switched applications, delay in seconds between redial attempts.

ty1250CfgNetDefNum2Dial.name: ty1250CfgNetDefNum2Dial
ty1250CfgNetDefNum2Dial.description: In switched applications, default phone number to dial. Numbers and dashes are allowed.

ty1250CfgNetBPVThresholding.name: ty1250CfgNetBPVThresholding
ty1250CfgNetBPVThresholding.description: Allows the user to turn on and off the BPV thresholding function. Valid values are thresholding_at_10E-4 (1) and disable-thresholding (2).

ty1250CfgDteType.name: ty1250CfgDteType
ty1250CfgDteType.description: The Dte channel type identifies the electrical specification of the interface. Read-only.

ty1250CfgDteClockInvert.name: ty1250CfgDteClockInvert
ty1250CfgDteClockInvert.description: Clock Inversion, invert-dte-clock (2), can be used to solve out of phase timing problems on DTE link. normal-dte-clock (1) can be used in most cases.

ty1250CfgDteTiming.name: ty1250CfgDteTiming
ty1250CfgDteTiming.description: The DTE channel Timing mode. Use loop2-timing (2) when in doubt.

ty1250CfgDialButton.name: ty1250CfgDialButton
ty1250CfgDialButton.description: In switched applications, Enables/Disables the button on front of unit. This button can used to manual answer an incomming call, or dial out the default number. The valid values are enable-button (1) and disable-button (2).

ty1250CfgDialDtr.name: ty1250CfgDialDtr
ty1250CfgDialDtr.description: In switched applications, Enables/Disables dialing on DTR signal transition. Valid values enable-dtr (1) and disable-dtr (2).

ty1250CfgDialRtsDisc.name: ty1250CfgDialRtsDisc
ty1250CfgDialRtsDisc.description: In switched applications, Enables/Disables disconnecting on RTS signal transition. Valid values are enable-rts (1) and disable-rts (2).

ty1250CfgDialRi.name: ty1250CfgDialRi
ty1250CfgDialRi.description: In switched applications, Enables/Disables incoming call notification to DTE via RI signal. Valid values are enable-ri (1) and disable-ri (2).

ty1250CfgMaintTable.name: ty1250CfgMaintTable
ty1250CfgMaintTable.description: The Maintenance Port Configuration table contains parameters for the Maintenance ports on the 1250. The Terminal Port is Index=1; SLIP port is 2

ty1250CfgMaintIndex.name: ty1250CfgMaintIndex
ty1250CfgMaintIndex.description: The Maintenance port under consideration. On the 1250, the Terminal Port is Index=1; SLIP port is 2.

ty1250CfgMaintMode.name: ty1250CfgMaintMode
ty1250CfgMaintMode.description: The Mode for this Maintenance Port. Values include ascii-vt100 (4), slip (7), and cslip (8).

ty1250CfgMaintBaud.name: ty1250CfgMaintBaud
ty1250CfgMaintBaud.description: Baud rate for this Maintenance port. Values are baud-2400 (2), baud-9600 (4), baud-19200 (5).

ty1250CfgMaintDataBits.name: ty1250CfgMaintDataBits
ty1250CfgMaintDataBits.description: Databits for this Maintenance port. Values are databits-7 (1) and databits-8 (2).

ty1250CfgMaintStopBits.name: ty1250CfgMaintStopBits
ty1250CfgMaintStopBits.description: Number of Stopbits for this Maintenance port. Values are stopbits-1 (1), stopbits-1-5 (2), and stopbits-2 (3).

ty1250CfgMaintParity.name: ty1250CfgMaintParity
ty1250CfgMaintParity.description: Parity for this Maintenance port. Values are no-parity (1), odd-parity (2), even-parity (3).

ty1250CfgMaintFlowCtrl.name: ty1250CfgMaintFlowCtrl
ty1250CfgMaintFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control for this Maintenance port. Values are no-flow-control (1), software-flow-control (2), and hardware-flow-control (3).

ty1250CfgSlipMyIP.name: ty1250CfgSlipMyIP
ty1250CfgSlipMyIP.description: The IP address for this node.

ty1250CfgSlipPeerIP.name: ty1250CfgSlipPeerIP
ty1250CfgSlipPeerIP.description: The IP address for other end of slip connection.

ty1250CfgSlipMask.name: ty1250CfgSlipMask
ty1250CfgSlipMask.description: The IP Network Mask (eg 255.255.255.0) for the SLIP link.

ty1250CfgSlipMaxMTU.name: ty1250CfgSlipMaxMTU
ty1250CfgSlipMaxMTU.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit is the size of the largest IP packet supported. This value should be set to the lowest value supported by any equipment in the transmission path. A size of 1006 (including header) is suggested.

ty1250CfgSnmpManagerIP.name: ty1250CfgSnmpManagerIP
ty1250CfgSnmpManagerIP.description: The IP address for the SNMP manager to receive this node's TRAPs.

ty1250CfgTelnetEnable.name: ty1250CfgTelnetEnable
ty1250CfgTelnetEnable.description: Enables/Disables the telnet feature. Valid values are enable-telnet (1) and disable-telnet (2).

ty1250CfgTelnetAutoLogOut.name: ty1250CfgTelnetAutoLogOut
ty1250CfgTelnetAutoLogOut.description: Enables/Disables the telnet auto-logout, logging out the user after a certain length of idle time. Valid values are autologout-at-15-minutes (1) and disable-autologout (2).

ty1250CallState.name: ty1250CallState
ty1250CallState.description: Call-related actions: a: Connect (initiate a call), b: Disconnect (terminate a call) c: Answer (answer an incoming call).

ty1250CallStatus.name: ty1250CallStatus
ty1250CallStatus.description: The call status is shown here.

ty1250CallNumber.name: ty1250CallNumber
ty1250CallNumber.description: The last phone number dialed out.

ty1250CallUpTime.name: ty1250CallUpTime
ty1250CallUpTime.description: Number of seconds the call has been up.

ty1250DiagUnitLocLoop.name: ty1250DiagUnitLocLoop
ty1250DiagUnitLocLoop.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the UNIT local loopback. This loopback occurs on all network ports transmit and receive logic. The unit will transmit DTE data out to the network as normal, and will also loop DTE data back to the DTE.

ty1250DiagUnitReset.name: ty1250DiagUnitReset
ty1250DiagUnitReset.description: Enables the operator to remotely reset the unit. Using this command will cause the unit to terminate all its connections and drop data.

ty1250DiagNetLineStatus.name: ty1250DiagNetLineStatus
ty1250DiagNetLineStatus.description: The Current status of the physical interface. Your network carrier can send Out-of-Service or Maintenance Mode codes.

ty1250DiagNetLclLpbk.name: ty1250DiagNetLclLpbk
ty1250DiagNetLclLpbk.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the network local loopback. This loopback occurs on the net side of the local transmit and receive logic. The unit continues to receive data from the network and also loops received data back to the network.

ty1250DiagNetRmtLpbk.name: ty1250DiagNetRmtLpbk
ty1250DiagNetRmtLpbk.description: Enables the operator to examine (ONLY) the status of network loopbacks placed by external equipment, such as your local CO. These loopbacks will loop received network data back out the network, disconnecting the DTE completely.

ty1250DiagDteSigRTS.name: ty1250DiagDteSigRTS
ty1250DiagDteSigRTS.description: The Dte Channel RTS signal. Values are rts-signal-on (1) and rts-signal-off (2).

ty1250DiagDteSigDTR.name: ty1250DiagDteSigDTR
ty1250DiagDteSigDTR.description: The Dte Channel DTR signal. Values are dtr-signal-on (1) and dtr-signal-off (2).

ty1250DiagDteLclLpbk.name: ty1250DiagDteLclLpbk
ty1250DiagDteLclLpbk.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local DTE Channel Loopback for the selected channel. This is will loop DTE data back towards the DTE interface in addition to passing it on to the network.

ty1250DiagDteV54Lpbk.name: ty1250DiagDteV54Lpbk
ty1250DiagDteV54Lpbk.description: This selection displays the status of the DTE Channel V.54 Loopback for the channel. This loopback is initiated by the remote node, causing this node to loop data back to the remote node.

ty1250DiagDteRmtV54Lpbk.name: ty1250DiagDteRmtV54Lpbk
ty1250DiagDteRmtV54Lpbk.description: This selection controls the DTE Channel V.54 Remote Loopback. Transmit-code-enable (3) will cause the node to transmit a V.54 code to the remote node which will then loop received data back to this node. transmit-code-disable (4) will transmit the disable code.

ty1250DiagDteBerState.name: ty1250DiagDteBerState
ty1250DiagDteBerState.description: BERT test related actions: a: Starts a BERT test on a channel, b: Stops a BERT test on a channel, c: Inject Errors while the BERT test is running, d: Clears BERT test errors.

ty1250DiagDteBerStatus.name: ty1250DiagDteBerStatus
ty1250DiagDteBerStatus.description: Displays the current BERT test sync status.

ty1250DiagDteBerErrors.name: ty1250DiagDteBerErrors
ty1250DiagDteBerErrors.description: Displays the number of errors detected in Bert Test.

ty1250DiagDteBerErrSec.name: ty1250DiagDteBerErrSec
ty1250DiagDteBerErrSec.description: Displays the number of seconds containing errors in BERT Test.

ty1250DiagDteBerTimeElaps.name: ty1250DiagDteBerTimeElaps
ty1250DiagDteBerTimeElaps.description: Elapsed time since BERT test was started or cleared.

ty1250DiagDteBerResyncs.name: ty1250DiagDteBerResyncs
ty1250DiagDteBerResyncs.description: Displays the number of times BERT test has synched up on the pattern.

ty1250StatsDteTxByteCount.name: ty1250StatsDteTxByteCount
ty1250StatsDteTxByteCount.description: The statistic counting the number of bytes transmitted on the DTE channel.

ty1250StatsDteRxByteCount.name: ty1250StatsDteRxByteCount
ty1250StatsDteRxByteCount.description: The statistic counting the number of bytes received on the DTE channel.

ty1250StatsDteClearStats.name: ty1250StatsDteClearStats
ty1250StatsDteClearStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the DTE statistics table.

ty1250StatsNetLoopLength.name: ty1250StatsNetLoopLength
ty1250StatsNetLoopLength.description: The statistic that estimates line attentuation on the network channel.

ty1250StatsNetBpvCount.name: ty1250StatsNetBpvCount
ty1250StatsNetBpvCount.description: The statistic counting the number of BPV errors on the network channel.

ty1250StatsNetTxByteCount.name: ty1250StatsNetTxByteCount
ty1250StatsNetTxByteCount.description: The statistic counting the number of bytes transmitted on the network channel.

ty1250StatsNetRxByteCount.name: ty1250StatsNetRxByteCount
ty1250StatsNetRxByteCount.description: The statistic counting the number of bytes received on the network channel.

ty1250StatsNetClearStats.name: ty1250StatsNetClearStats
ty1250StatsNetClearStats.description: Allows the user to zero out all the statistics in the network statistics table.

ty1250AlarmType.name: ty1250AlarmType
ty1250AlarmType.description: The type of alarms that are generated on the node

ty1250Trap.name: ty1250Trap
ty1250Trap.description: A ty1250Trap trap signifies that the sending node had its `ty1250AlarmType` variable modified.

ty1250LineInServiceTrap.name: ty1250LineInServiceTrap
ty1250LineInServiceTrap.description: The line is back in service.

ty1250BadConfigTrap.name: ty1250BadConfigTrap
ty1250BadConfigTrap.description: The configuration specified in the SET command was bad. SET failed.

ty1250LocalConfigTrap.name: ty1250LocalConfigTrap
ty1250LocalConfigTrap.description: The configuration has been changed by a means other than SNMP.

ty1250V54LoopUpInitiatedTrap.name: ty1250V54LoopUpInitiatedTrap
ty1250V54LoopUpInitiatedTrap.description: Starting to loop up a V54 loopback on the remote unit.

ty1250V54LoopDownCompletedTrap.name: ty1250V54LoopDownCompletedTrap
ty1250V54LoopDownCompletedTrap.description: Completed the loop down of a V54 loopback on the remote unit.

ty1250V54LoopbackEnabledTrap.name: ty1250V54LoopbackEnabledTrap
ty1250V54LoopbackEnabledTrap.description: V54 loopback enabled by remote unit.

ty1250V54LoopbackDisabledTrap.name: ty1250V54LoopbackDisabledTrap
ty1250V54LoopbackDisabledTrap.description: V54 loopback disabled by remote unit.

ty1250LocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap.name: ty1250LocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap
ty1250LocalUnitLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Unable to do a local unit loopback.

ty1250LocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap.name: ty1250LocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap
ty1250LocalNetLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Unable to do a local network loopback.

ty1250LocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap.name: ty1250LocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap
ty1250LocalDteLoopbackFailedTrap.description: Unable to do a local DTE loopback.

ty1250V54LoopbackFailedTrap.name: ty1250V54LoopbackFailedTrap
ty1250V54LoopbackFailedTrap.description: Unable to do a V54 loopback.
